<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 3:23AM EDT  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED FIRE WEATHER POTENTIAL TODAY...
Mostly sunny skies with northwesterly winds between 25 and 30 mph
and low relative humidity values between 25 and 30 percent has
raised concerns about elevated fire weather potential today.
Open burning is not recommended today. Follow instructions of
local fire wardens. Be very careful when handling and disposing of
ignition sources outdoors, such as cigarettes or matches.</description>
